  "body": "Inspired from a discussion on Discord: https://discord.com/channels/697535391594446898/697539289042649190/1128622402822213692\r\n\r\nAfter a primary BN is recovering from network outage/restart, it would be good to be able to configure VC to switch back to primary only when certain amount of peers is met. This will allow for a smoother failover. A standard beacon api endpoint could be used to get the peer count: https://ethereum.github.io/beacon-APIs/?urls.primaryName=dev#/Node/getPeerCount",
